Meetings

Building Applications with Redis

September 08, 2014 at 6pm - Brad Young

Redis is an open source, advanced key-value cache and store. I will cover the basics on using Redis for caching, NoSQL database and pub/sub messaging.

Locations

  • Murray State University, Business Building, Room 551
  • Murray State University, Paducah Campus, Room 215 (via video)

AngularJS, TypeScript with ASP.NET MVC

October 13, 2014 at 6pm - Brad Young

We will look at how to build a web application using AngularJS, TypeScript, ASP.NET MVC and use Redis for data storage and notifications.

Locations

  • Murray State University, Business Building, IPTV Room 102
  • Murray State University, Paducah Campus, IPTV Room 139 (via video)

REST, Hypermedia, and HTTP

November 10, 2014 at 6pm - Stephen Mizell

We will take a look through history at the first conception of the internet, how the web architecture works, and how using hypermedia can provide the means to have a really great, scalable, evolvable API.

Locations

  • Murray State University, Business Building, IPTV Room 102
  • Murray State University, Paducah Campus, IPTV Room 139 (via video)

Fun with Functional Programming

December 08, 2014 at 6pm - Stephen Mizell

We will take a look at functional programming and how it can be helpful in common languages like JavaScript.

Locations

  • Murray State University, Business Building, IPTV Room 102
  • Murray State University, Paducah Campus, IPTV Room 139 (via video)
